declarations.comments: A newtype for numbers in the closed interval from 0.0 and 1.0.
declarations.title: SmallNumber

declarations.comments: A newtype for small integer values in the range from 0 to 100.
declarations.title: SmallInt

declarations.comments:
A data type that describes possible output actions and values for an
interactive test.
declarations.title: Renderable

declarations.comments: A newtype for non-negative integer values.
declarations.title: NonNegativeInt

declarations.comments:
A newtype for strings where "\n" is parsed as a newline
(instead of "\\n").
declarations.title: Multiline

declarations.comments:
A type class for input parameters for interactive tests. Instances for
type `a` must provide a way to create a Flare UI which holds a value of
type `a`.
declarations.title: Flammable

declarations.comments:
A type class for interactive tests. Instances must provide a way to create
a Flare UI which returns a `Renderable` output.
declarations.title: Interactive

declarations.comments:
A class for types which can be parsed from a `String`. This class is used
to construct input fields for `Array a` and `List a`.
declarations.title: Read

declarations.comments: A default `interactive` implementation for any `Show`able type.
declarations.title: interactiveShow

declarations.comments: A default `interactive` implementation for types with a `Generic` instance.
declarations.title: interactiveGeneric

declarations.comments:
Run an interactive test. The ID specifies the parent element to which
the test will be appended and the label provides a title for the test.
declarations.title: flareCheck'

declarations.comments: Run an interactive test. The label provides a title for the test.
declarations.title: flareCheck

declarations.comments: Parse a package description and run the interactive documentation.
declarations.title: withPackage

declarations.comments: Like `flareDoc`, but the HTML element can be specified.
declarations.title: flareDoc'

declarations.comments:
Add an interactive documentation entry. The `String` arguments specify the
module name and the function name, respectively.
declarations.title: flareDoc
